The Oil and Gas Trainers Association of Nigeria has said it will examine the issue of human capacity development in the nation’s oil industry at its forthcoming lecture. The President, OGTAN, Mr Mayowa Afe, disclosed this at a press briefing on Tuesday ahead of its 2021 Annual General Meeting/Lecture series slated for next week in Lagos. He said the event, themed ‘Inclusive Human Capacity Development’, was one of the association‘s key events for the year. He said the Executive Secretary of Nigerian Content Development and Monitoring Board would deliver the keynote speech on sustaining indigenous participation in the oil and gas industry through knowledge and technology transfer. Afe said following the declaration of the ‘Decade of Gas’, the Director/Chief Executive Officer, DPR, Auwalu Sarki, as the guest speaker, would speak on human capacity development opportunities in the government gas expansion programme. He said the association would honour the Minister of State for Petroleum Resources, Timipre Sylva, with ‘The Gas Decade Personality Award’ in recognition of his contributions towards the development of Nigeria as a gas-based economy and the transition to a cleaner source of energy in alignment with the global energy transition. He said, “The association will also decorate the Director/CEO DPR with “The Oil and Gas Innovative Award’ in recognition of his numerous contributions and innovation that have led to the build-up toward our national goals, in aligning with the global energy transition and bring stability and expansion and participation to the national economy.’ Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com